      public void setUserStoryId()

    • addUserStory

      public int addUserStory(String title, String user, String action, String value)
      Creates a new UserStory in the submitted state, adds it to the list in sorted order, and returns the id. If a story already exists with the given id, an IllegalArgumentException will be thrown.
      Parameters:
      title - story's title
      user - story's user information
      action - story's action information
      value - story's value information
      Returns:
      id the id of the newly added user story
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if a story already exists in the list with the given id

    • addUserStory

      public void addUserStory(UserStory story)
      Adds the user story to the list in sorted order by id. The list will be maintained in sorted order, so you will be able to add a new story in order. If a story already exists with the given id, an IllegalArgumentException will be thrown.
      Parameters:
      story - story to be added to the list
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if a story already exists in the list with the given id

    • getUserStoryById

      public UserStory getUserStoryById(int id)
      Returns the UserStory in the list with the given id. If there is no UserStory with that id, the method returns null.
      Parameters:
      id - id to match with the UserStory in the list
      Returns:
      the UserStory with the matching id, or null if there are no matching UserStories

    • deleteUserStoryById

      public void deleteUserStoryById(int id)
      Removes the UserStory with the given id from the list.
      Parameters:
      id - given id to match with the UserStory in the list

    • executeCommand

      public void executeCommand(int id, Command c)
      Finds the UserStory with the given id and updates it by passing in the given Command.
      Parameters:
      id - given id to match with the UserStory in the list
      c - command to give to the found UserStory
